============================================================
  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Boyle's Law
Formula: P₁V₁ = P₂V₂
Note:    Pressure and volume inversely proportional at constant T

Domain:  Astronomy
Topic:   Schwarzschild Radius
Formula: r_s = 2GM/c²
Note:    Event horizon radius of a black hole

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   Cell Theory
Formula: All life is made of cells arising from pre-existing cells
Note:    Foundation of modern biology

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   Central Dogma
Formula: DNA → RNA → Protein
Note:    Information flow in all living organisms

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   Photosynthesis
Formula: 6CO₂+6H₂O+light→C₆H₁₂O₆+6O₂
Note:    How plants produce energy from sunlight

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Prime Number Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      π(n) ~ n/ln(n)
Applications: Cryptography, algorithm analysis
Discoverer:   Hadamard/de la VP (1896)

Theorem/Law:  Central Limit Theorem
Branch:       Statistics
Formula:      Sample means approach normal distribution
Applications: Polling, quality control, finance
Discoverer:   Lyapunov (1901)

Theorem/Law:  Fermat's Last Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      aⁿ + bⁿ ≠ cⁿ for n>2
Applications: Advanced number theory, elliptic curves
Discoverer:   Fermat (conjecture); Wiles (proof) (1637)

